* For each group of `SpeedLimit`, either the number of observations is at least 30 \underline{or} the observations appear (roughly) normally distributed.
* For each group of `SpeedLimit`, the observations are drawn from a population with the \underline{same variance} (that is, the sample standard deviations or spreads of each group seem similar).
* The observations within each group of `SpeedLimit` are independent. 
* The observations across the groups of `SpeedLimit` are independent. 

